subSubSection.paragraph:
Females lack epigynum. The opening of the female genitalia is formed by a fold of the abdomen cuticle that carries setae on its dorsal side (the actual genital opening is shifted to the end of this fold; fig. 7). Spermathecae absent or vestigial. The uterus externus connects via an enlarged chamber with a nonpaired membranous structure that has a posterior sac (a nonpaired sperm storage organ) (see also 
Dimitrov et al., 2007
).
